?value: A supranuclear gaze palsy is an inability to look in a particular direction as a result of cerebral impairment. There is a loss of the voluntary aspect of eye movements, but, as the brainstem is still intact, all the reflex conjugate eye movements are normal.

?translation: La paralysie supranucléaire du regard est une incapacité à regarder dans une direction particulière résultant d'une déficience cérébrale. ?value: Cleft of the soft palate (also known as the velum, or muscular palate) as a result of a developmental defect occurring between the 7th and 12th week of pregnancy. Cleft soft palate can cause functional abnormalities of the Eustachian tube with resulting middle ear anomalies and hearing difficulties, as well as speech problems associated with hypernasal speech due to velopharyngeal insufficiency.
?source_value: Cleft of the soft palate (also known as the velum, or muscular palate) as a result of a developmental defect occurring between the 7th and 12th week of pregnancy. Cleft soft palate can cause functional abnormalities of the Eustachian tube with resulting middle ear anomalies and hearing difficulties, as well as speech problems associated with hypernasal speech due to velopharyngeal insufficiency
?translation: Fente du palais mou (également appelée vélum ou palais musculaire) résultant d'un défaut de développement survenant entre la 7e et la 12e semaine de grossesse. La fente palatine peut entraîner des anomalies fonctionnelles de la trompe d'Eustache, avec pour conséquence des anomalies de l'oreille moyenne et des difficultés d'audition, ainsi que des problèmes d'élocution associés à une élocution hypernasale due à une insuffisance vélopharyngée.@fr

?value: An inherited retinal disease subtype in which the rod photoreceptors appear to be more severely affected than the cone photoreceptors. Typical presentation is with nyctalopia (due to rod dysfunction) followed by loss of mid-peripheral field of vision, which gradually extends and leaves many patients with a small central island of vision due to the preservation of macular cones.
?source_value: An inherited retinal disease subtype in which the rod photoreceptors appear to be more severely affected than the cone photoreceptors. Typical presentation is with nyctalopia (due to rod dysfunction) followed by loss of mid-peripheral field of vision, which gradually extends and leaves many patients with a small central island of vision due to the preservation of macular cones
?translation: Un sous-type de maladie rétinienne héréditaire dans laquelle les photorécepteurs à bâtonnets semblent être plus gravement touchés que les photorécepteurs à cônes. La présentation typique est une nyctalopie (due au dysfonctionnement des bâtonnets) suivie d'une perte du champ de vision périphérique moyen, qui s'étend progressivement et laisse à de nombreux patients un petit îlot de vision centrale en raison de la préservation des cônes maculaires.@fr

?value: The presence of a cleft in the oral cavity, the two main types of which are cleft lip and cleft palate. In cleft lip, there is the congenital failure of the maxillary and median nasal processes to fuse, forming a groove or fissure in the lip. In cleft palate, there is a congenital failure of the palate to fuse properly, forming a grooved depression or fissure in the roof of the mouth. Clefts of the lip and palate can occur individually or together. It is preferable to code each defect separately.
?source_value: The presence of a cleft in the oral cavity, the two main types of which are cleft lip and cleft palate. In cleft lip, there is the congenital failure of the maxillary and median nasal processes to fuse, forming a groove or fissure in the lip. In cleft palate, there is a congenital failure of the palate to fuse properly, forming a grooved depression or fissure in the roof of the mouth. Clefts of the lip and palate can occur individually or together. It is preferable to code each defect separately
?translation: La présence d'une fente dans la cavité buccale, dont les deux principaux types sont la fente labiale et la fente palatine. Dans le cas d'une fente labiale, il y a un défaut congénital de fusion entre les processus maxillaire et nasal médian, ce qui forme un sillon ou une fissure dans la lèvre. Dans le cas de la fente palatine, il y a un défaut congénital de fusion du palais, ce qui forme une dépression ou une fissure dans le palais. Les fentes labiales et palatines peuvent se produire individuellement ou ensemble. Il est préférable de coder chaque défaut séparément@fr

?value: A genital phenotype that is not clearly assignable to a single gender. Ambiguous genitalia can be evaluated using the Prader scale: Prader 0: Normal female external genitalia. Prader 1: Female external genitalia with clitoromegaly. Prader 2: Clitoromegaly with partial labial fusion forming a funnel-shaped urogenital sinus. Prader 3: Increased phallic enlargement. Complete labioscrotal fusion forming a urogenital sinus with a single opening. Prader 4: Complete scrotal fusion with urogenital opening at the base or on the shaft of the phallus. Prader 5: Normal male external genitalia. The diagnosis of ambiguous genitalia is made for Prader 1-4.
?source_value: A genital phenotype that is not clearly assignable to a single gender. Ambiguous genitalia can be evaluated using the Prader scale: Prader 0: Normal female external genitalia. Prader 1: Female external genitalia with clitoromegaly. Prader 2: Clitoromegaly with partial labial fusion forming a funnel-shaped urogenital sinus. Prader 3: Increased phallic enlargement. Complete labioscrotal fusion forming a urogenital sinus with a single opening. Prader 4: Complete scrotal fusion with urogenital opening at the base or on the shaft of the phallus. Prader 5: Normal male external genitalia. The diagnosis of ambiguous genitalia is made for Prader 1-4
?translation: Phénotype génital qui ne peut être clairement attribué à un seul sexe. Les organes génitaux ambigus peuvent être évalués à l'aide de l'échelle de Prader : Prader 0 : Organes génitaux externes féminins normaux. Prader 1 : Organes génitaux externes féminins avec clitoromégalie. Prader 2 : Clitoromégalie avec fusion labiale partielle formant un sinus urogénital en forme d'entonnoir. Prader 3 : Augmentation de l'hypertrophie phallique. Fusion labioscrotale complète formant un sinus urogénital à ouverture unique. Prader 4 : Fusion scrotale complète avec ouverture urogénitale à la base ou sur la tige du pénis. Prader 5 : Organes génitaux externes masculins normaux. Le diagnostic d'organes génitaux ambigus est posé pour les cas Prader 1-4.@fr

?translation: Dans le cas d'une partition II incomplète, la cochlée est constituée de 1,5 tour ; les tours apicaux et médians de la cochlée sont indifférenciés et forment un apex kystique. ?value: A supranuclear gaze palsy is an inability to look in a vertical direction as a result of cerebral impairment. There is a loss of the voluntary aspect of eye movements, but, as the brainstem is still intact, all the reflex conjugate eye movements are normal.

?translation: La paralysie supranucléaire du regard est une incapacité à regarder dans une direction verticale résultant d'une déficience cérébrale. Il y a une perte de l'aspect volontaire des mouvements oculaires, mais, comme le tronc cérébral est encore intact, tous les mouvements oculaires conjugués réflexes sont normaux.@fr

?value: Absence or abnormal closure of the choana (the posterior nasal aperture). Most embryologists believe that posterior choanal atresia results from a failure of rupture between the 35th and 38th day of fetal life of the partition which separates the bucconasal or buccopharyngeal membranes. The resultant choanal atresia may be unilateral or bilateral, bony or membranous, complete or incomplete. In over 90 per cent of cases the obstruction is bony, while in the remainder it is membranous. The bony type of atresia is commonly located 1-2 mm. anterior to the posterior edge of the hard palate, and the osseous septum varies in thickness from 1 to 10 mm. In the membranous form of choanal atresia the obstruction usually occurs further posteriorly. In approximately one third of cases the atresia is bilateral.
?source_value: Absence or abnormal closure of the choana (the posterior nasal aperture)
?translation: Absence ou fermeture anormale des choanes (l'ouverture nasale postérieure)@fr

?value: A thickening of the skin thickness in the posterior aspect of the fetal neck. A nuchal fold (NF) measurement is obtained in a transverse section of the fetal head at the level of the cavum septum pellucidum and thalami, angled posteriorly to include the cerebellum. The measurement is taken from the outer edge of the occiput bone to the outer skin limit directly in the midline. An NF measurement greater than 5 mm at 14 to 17+6 weeks of gestation, or 6 mm at 18 to 28 weeks has been associated with a markedly increased risk for Down syndrome.
?source_value: A thickening of the skin thickness in the posterior aspect of the fetal neck. A nuchal fold measurement is obtained in a transverse section of the fetal head at the level of the cavum septum pellucidum and thalami, angled posteriorly to include the cerebellum. The measurement is taken from the outer edge of the occiput bone to the outer skin limit directly in the midline. A measurement 6 mm or more is considered significant between 18 and 24 weeks and a measurement of 5 mm or more is considered significant at 16 to 18 weeks (pmid:16100637)
?translation: Un épaississement de l'épaisseur de la peau dans la partie postérieure du cou du fœtus. La mesure du pli nucal est obtenue sur une coupe transversale de la tête du fœtus au niveau du septum pellucidum et des thalami, inclinée vers l'arrière pour inclure le cervelet. La mesure est prise du bord externe de l'os occipital à la limite externe de la peau, directement sur la ligne médiane. Une mesure de 6 mm ou plus est considérée comme significative entre 18 et 24 semaines et une mesure de 5 mm ou plus est considérée comme significative entre 16 et 18 semaines (pmid:16100637).@fr

?value: In newborns, the two frontal bones, two parietal bones, and one occipital bone are joined by fibrous sutures, which form a small posterior fontanelle, and a larger, diamond-shaped anterior fontanelle. These regions allow for the skull to pass the birth canal and for later growth. The fontanelles gradually ossify, whereby the posterior fontanelle usually closes by eight weeks and the anterior fontanelle by the 9th to 16th month of age. Large fontanelles are diagnosed if the fontanelles are larger than age-dependent norms.
?source_value: In newborns, the two frontal bones, two parietal bones, and one occipital bone are joined by fibrous sutures, which form a small posterior fontanelle, and a larger, diamond-shaped anterior fontanelle. These regions allow for the skull to pass the birth canal and for later growth. The fontanelles gradually ossify, whereby the posterior fontanelle usually closes by eight weeks and the anterior fontanelle by the 9th to 16th month of age. Large fontanelles are diagnosed if the fontanelles are larger than age-dependent norms
?translation: Chez les nouveau-nés, les deux os frontaux, les deux os pariétaux et l'os occipital sont reliés par des sutures fibreuses, qui forment une petite fontanelle postérieure et une fontanelle antérieure plus grande, en forme de losange. Ces régions permettent le passage du crâne dans le canal de naissance et sa croissance ultérieure. Les fontanelles s'ossifient progressivement, la fontanelle postérieure se fermant généralement vers huit semaines et la fontanelle antérieure vers le 9e ou le 16e mois. On diagnostique des fontanelles de grande taille si les fontanelles sont plus grandes que les normes liées à l'âge.@fr

?value: An abnormality of skull shape characterized by a increased anterior-posterior diameter, i.e., an increased antero-posterior dimension of the skull. Cephalic index less than 76%. Alternatively, an apparently increased antero-posterior length of the head compared to width. Often due to premature closure of the sagittal suture.
?source_value: An abnormality of skull shape characterized by a increased anterior-posterior diameter, i.e., an increased antero-posterior dimension of the skull. Cephalic index less than 76%. Alternatively, an apparently increased antero-posterior length of the head compared to width. Often due to premature closure of the sagittal suture
?translation: Une anomalie de la forme du crâne caractérisée par une augmentation du diamètre antéro-postérieur, c'est-à-dire une augmentation de la dimension antéro-postérieure du crâne. Un indice céphalique inférieur à 76 %. Alternativement, une longueur antéro-postérieure de la tête apparemment accrue par rapport à la largeur. Souvent due à une fermeture prématurée de la suture sagittale.@fr

?value: A unilateral form of agenesis of the kidney.
?source_value: A unilateral form of agenesis of the kidney

?value: A type of hearing impairment in one or both ears related to an abnormal functionality of the cochlear nerve.
?source_value: A type of hearing impairment in one or both ears related to an abnormal functionality of the cochlear nerve
?translation: Type de déficience auditive dans une ou deux oreilles, liée à une fonctionnalité anormale du nerf cochléaire.@fr

?value: Flat skin surface, with no ridge formation in the central region of the upper lip between the nasal base and upper vermilion border.
?source_value: Flat skin surface, with no ridge formation in the central region of the upper lip between the nasal base and upper vermilion border
?translation: Surface cutanée plate, sans formation de crête dans la région centrale de la lèvre supérieure, entre la base du nez et le bord supérieur du vermillon.@fr

?value: Any anomaly of the function of the endocrine system.
?source_value: Any anomaly of the function of the endocrine system
?translation: Toute anomalie de fonction du système endocrinien@fr

?value: An abnormality of the chin, i.e., of the inferior portion of the face lying inferior to the lower lip and including the central prominence of the lower jaw.
?source_value: An abnormality of the chin, i.e., of the inferior portion of the face lying inferior to the lower lip and including the central prominence of the lower jaw
?translation: Anomalie du menton, c'est-à-dire de la partie inférieure du visage située en dessous de la lèvre inférieure et comprenant la proéminence centrale de la mâchoire inférieure.@fr

?value: A face with a rounded and slightly elongated outline.
?source_value: A face with a rounded and slightly elongated outline
?translation: Un visage au contour arrondi et légèrement allongé.@fr

?value: Abnormality of the anterior chamber, which is the space in the eye that is behind the cornea and in front of the iris.
?source_value: Abnormality of the anterior chamber, which is the space in the eye that is behind the cornea and in front of the iris
?translation: Anomalie de la chambre antérieure, qui est l'espace de l'œil situé derrière la cornée et devant l'iris@fr

?value: A developmental defect characterized by a cleft of some portion of the eye or ocular adnexa.
?source_value: A developmental defect characterized by a cleft of some portion of the eye or ocular adnexa
?translation: Défaut de développement caractérisé par une fente d'une partie de l'œil ou de l'annexe oculaire.@fr

?value: Inflammation of the paranasal sinuses owing to a viral, bacterial, or fungal infection, allergy, or an autoimmune reaction.
?source_value: Inflammation of the paranasal sinuses owing to a viral, bacterial, or fungal infection, allergy, or an autoimmune reaction
?translation: Inflammation des sinus paranasaux due à une infection virale, bactérienne ou fongique, à une allergie ou à une réaction auto-immune.@fr

?value: Abnormality of the nasal bridge, which is the saddle-shaped area that includes the nasal root and the lateral aspects of the nose. It lies between the glabella and the inferior boundary of the nasal bone, and extends laterally to the inner canthi.
?source_value: Abnormality of the nasal bridge, which is the saddle-shaped area that includes the nasal root and the lateral aspects of the nose. It lies between the glabella and the inferior boundary of the nasal bone, and extends laterally to the inner canthi
?translation: Anomalie de l'arête nasale, qui est la zone en forme de selle qui comprend la racine du nez et les aspects latéraux du nez. Elle se situe entre la glabelle et la limite inférieure de l'os nasal, et s'étend latéralement jusqu'à la canthi interne.@fr

?value: A degree of kidney failure severe enough to require dialysis or kidney transplantation for survival characterized by a severe reduction in glomerular filtration rate (less than 15 ml/min/1.73 m2) and other manifestations including increased serum creatinine.
?source_value: A degree of kidney failure severe enough to require dialysis or kidney transplantation for survival characterized by a severe reduction in glomerular filtration rate (less than 15 ml/min/1.73 m2) and other manifestations including increased serum creatinine
?translation: Maladie rénale chronique, avec insuffisance rénale chronique de stade 5@fr

?value: A height above that which is expected according to age and gender norms.
?source_value: A height above that which is expected according to age and gender norms
?translation: Taille supérieure à la taille attendue selon les normes d'âge et de genre@fr

?value: Telangiectasia (that is, the presence of small dilated superficial blood vessels) of the lips.
?source_value: Telangiectasia (that is, the presence of small dilated superficial blood vessels) of the lips
?translation: Télangiectasie (c'est-à-dire la présence de petits vaisseaux sanguins superficiels dilatés) des lèvres.@fr

?value: Any structural abnormality of the choroid.
?source_value: Any structural abnormality of the choroid
?translation: Toute anomalie structurelle de la choroïde@fr

?value: Abnormality of the pituitary gland (also known as hypophysis), which is an endocrine gland that protrudes from the bottom of the hypothalamus at the base of the brain. The pituitary gland secretes the hormones ACTH, TSH, PRL, GH, endorphins, FSH, LH, oxytocin, and antidiuretic hormone. The secretion of hormones from the anterior pituitary is under the strict control of hypothalamic hormones, and the posterior pituitary is essentially an extension of the hypothalamus, so that hypothalamus and pituitary gland may be regarded as a functional unit.
?source_value: Abnormality of the pituitary gland (also known as hypophysis), which is an endocrine gland that protrudes from the bottom of the hypothalamus at the base of the brain. The pituitary gland secretes the hormones ACTH, TSH, PRL, GH, endorphins, FSH, LH, oxytocin, and antidiuretic hormone. The secretion of hormones from the anterior pituitary is under the strict control of hypothalamic hormones, and the posterior pituitary is essentially an extension of the hypothalamus, so that hypothalamus and pituitary gland may be regarded as a functional unit
?translation: Anomalie de la glande pituitaire (nommée aussi hypophyse), qui est une glande endocrine située sous l'hypothalamus, à la base du cerveau. L'hypophyse sécrète les hormones ACTH, TSH, PRL, GH, FSH, LH, ocytocine et ADH. La sécrétion d'hormones anté-hypophysaires (adéno-hypophyse) est sous le contrôle privilégié des hormones hypothalamiques et la post-hypophyse (neuro-hypophyse) est essentiellement une extension de l'hypothalamus, de sorte que l'hypothalamus et la glande pituitaire peuvent être considérés comme une unité fonctionnelle@fr

?value: Parietal bossing is a marked prominence in the parietal region.
?source_value: Parietal bossing is a marked prominence in the parietal region
?translation: La bosse pariétale est une proéminence marquée dans la région pariétale.@fr

?value: Increased inferior-superior length of the neck.
?source_value: Increased inferior-superior length of the neck
?translation: Augmentation de la longueur inféro-supérieure du cou.@fr

?value: An abnormally slow velocity of the saccadic eye movements.
?source_value: An abnormally slow velocity of the saccadic eye movements
?translation: Une vitesse anormalement lente des mouvements saccadés des yeux.@fr

?value: A duplication of the collecting system of the kidney, defined as a kidney with two (instead of, normally, one) pyelocaliceal systems. The pyelocaliceal system is comprised of the renal pelvis and calices. The duplicated renal collecting system can be associated with a single ureter or with double ureters. In the latter case, the two ureters empty separately into the bladder or fuse to form a single ureteral orifice.
?source_value: A duplication of the collecting system of the kidney, defined as a kidney with two (instead of, normally, one) pyelocaliceal systems. The pyelocaliceal system is comprised of the renal pelvis and calices. The duplicated renal collecting system can be associated with a single ureter or with double ureters. In the latter case, the two ureters empty separately into the bladder or fuse to form a single ureteral orifice
?translation: Une duplication du système collecteur du rein, défini comme un rein avec deux (au lieu d'un seul, normalement) systèmes pyélocaliciaires. Le système pyélocaliciel est composé du bassin rénal et des calices. Le système collecteur rénal dédoublé peut être associé à un seul uretère ou à des uretères doubles. Dans ce dernier cas, les deux uretères se jettent séparément dans la vessie ou fusionnent pour former un seul orifice urétéral.@fr

?value: Multicystic dysplasia of the kidney is characterized by multiple cysts of varying size in the kidney and the absence of a normal pelvicaliceal system. The condition is associated with ureteral or ureteropelvic atresia, and the affected kidney is nonfunctional.
?source_value: Multicystic dysplasia of the kidney is characterized by multiple cysts of varying size in the kidney and the absence of a normal pelvicaliceal system. The condition is associated with ureteral or ureteropelvic atresia, and the affected kidney is nonfunctional
?translation: La dysplasie rénale multikystique est caractérisée par la présence de multiples kystes de taille variable et par l'absence d'un système pyélocaliciel normal. Cette maladie est associée à une atrésie urétérale ou urétéropelvique et le rein touché est non-fonctionnel@fr

?value: Loss of the ability to control the urinary bladder leading to involuntary urination.
?source_value: Loss of the ability to control the urinary bladder leading to involuntary urination
?translation: Perte de la capacité à contrôler la vessie conduisant à une miction involontaire@fr

?value: Distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border.
?source_value: Distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border
?translation: Distance entre la base du nez et le bord vermillon de la ligne médiane de la lèvre supérieure supérieure supérieure supérieure de plus de 2 écarts types à la moyenne. Ou encore, une distance apparemment accrue entre la base du nez et le bord vermillon de la ligne médiane de la lèvre supérieure.@fr

?value: Increase in width of the nasal tip.
?source_value: Increase in width of the nasal tip
?translation: Augmentation de la largeur de la pointe nasale@fr

?value: Reduced depth of the anterior chamber, i.e., the anteroposterior distance between the cornea and the iris is decreased.
?source_value: Reduced depth of the anterior chamber, i.e., the anteroposterior distance between the cornea and the iris is decreased
?translation: Réduction de la profondeur de la chambre antérieure, c'est-à-dire diminution de la distance antéropostérieure entre la cornée et l'iris.@fr

?value: An abnormality of eye movement characterized by impairment of fast (saccadic) eye movements.
?source_value: An abnormality of eye movement characterized by impairment of fast (saccadic) eye movements
?translation: Anomalie des mouvements oculaires caractérisée par une altération des mouvements oculaires rapides (saccades).@fr

?value: Visual impairment (or vision impairment) is vision loss (of a person) to such a degree as to qualify as an additional support need through a significant limitation of visual capability resulting from either disease, trauma, or congenital or degenerative conditions that cannot be corrected by conventional means, such as refractive correction, medication, or surgery.
?source_value: Visual impairment (or vision impairment) is vision loss (of a person) to such a degree as to qualify as an additional support need through a significant limitation of visual capability resulting from either disease, trauma, or congenital or degenerative conditions that cannot be corrected by conventional means, such as refractive correction, medication, or surgery
?translation: La déficience visuelle (ou trouble de la vision) est une perte de vision (d'une personne) à un degré tel qu'elle peut être considérée comme un besoin d'aide supplémentaire en raison d'une limitation significative de la capacité visuelle résultant d'une maladie, d'un traumatisme ou d'une affection congénitale ou dégénérative qui ne peut être corrigée par des moyens conventionnels, tels qu'une correction réfractive, des médicaments ou une intervention chirurgicale.@fr

?value: An abnormal narrowing of the external auditory canal.
?source_value: An abnormal narrowing of the external auditory canal
?translation: Un rétrécissement anormal du conduit auditif externe.@fr

?value: Erosion of the mucous mebrane of the mouth with local excavation of the surface, resulting from the sloughing of inflammatory necrotic tissue.
?source_value: Erosion of the mucous mebrane of the mouth with local excavation of the surface, resulting from the sloughing of inflammatory necrotic tissue
?translation: Érosion de la muqueuse buccale avec excavation locale de la surface, résultant de la desquamation du tissu nécrotique inflammatoire.@fr

?value: A cataract is an opacity or clouding that develops in the crystalline lens of the eye or in its capsule.
?source_value: A cataract is an opacity or clouding that develops in the crystalline lens of the eye or in its capsule
?translation: Une cataracte est une opacité ou un trouble qui se développe dans le cristallin de l'œil ou dans sa capsule.@fr

?value: Lack of prominence of the nose resulting from a posteriorly-placed nasal ridge.
?source_value: Lack of prominence of the nose resulting from a posteriorly-placed nasal ridge
?translation: Manque de proéminence du nez résultant d'une crête nasale placée en arrière.@fr

?value: Median longitudinal ear length greater than two standard deviations above the mean and median ear width greater than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or, apparent increase in length and width of the pinna (subjective).
?source_value: Median longitudinal ear length greater than two standard deviations above the mean and median ear width greater than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or, apparent increase in length and width of the pinna (subjective)
?translation: Longueur longitudinale médiane de l'oreille supérieure à deux écarts-types au-dessus de la moyenne et largeur médiane de l'oreille supérieure à deux écarts-types au-dessus de la moyenne (objectif) ; ou augmentation apparente de la longueur et de la largeur du pavillon de l'oreille (subjectif).@fr

?value: An anomalous response to a test that is designed to probe the function of the endocrine system.
?source_value: An anomalous response to a test that is designed to probe the function of the endocrine system
?translation: Réponse anormale à un test conçu pour vérifier une fonction du système endocrinien@fr

?value: A structural abnormality of the retina.
?source_value: A structural abnormality of the retina
?translation: Une anomalie structurale de la rétine@fr

?value: An abnormality of the mastoid process, which is the conical prominence projecting from the undersurface of the mastoid portion of the temporal bone.
?source_value: An abnormality of the mastoid process, which is the conical prominence projecting from the undersurface of the mastoid portion of the temporal bone
?translation: Anomalie de l'apophyse mastoïde, qui est la proéminence conique faisant saillie sur la surface inférieure de la partie mastoïde de l'os temporal.@fr

?value: Increased volume and globular shape of the anteroinferior aspect of the nose.
?source_value: Increased volume and globular shape of the anteroinferior aspect of the nose
?translation: Augmentation du volume et forme globulaire de la face antéro-inférieure du nez.@fr

?value: In otosclerosis, a callus of bone accumulates on the stapes creating a partial fixation. This limits the movement of the stapes bone, which results in hearing loss.
?source_value: In otosclerosis, a callus of bone accumulates on the stapes creating a partial fixation. This limits the movement of the stapes bone, which results in hearing loss
?translation: Dans l'otospongiose, un cal osseux s'accumule sur l'étrier, créant une fixation partielle. Cela limite le mouvement de l'étrier, ce qui entraîne une perte d'audition.@fr

?value: Congenital anomaly characterized by closure or failure to develop an opening in the urethra in females.
?source_value: Congenital anomaly characterized by closure or failure to develop an opening in the urethra in females
?translation: Anomalie congénitale caractérisée par la fermeture ou l'absence d'ouverture de l'urètre chez la femme.@fr

?value: Progressive microcephaly is diagnosed when the head circumference falls progressively behind age- and gender-dependent norms.
?source_value: Progressive microcephaly is diagnosed when the head circumference falls progressively behind age- and gender-dependent norms
?translation: Une microcéphalie progressive est diagnostiquée lorsque le périmètre crânien est progressivement inférieur aux normes établies en fonction de l'âge et du sexe.@fr

?value: Loss of visual acuity (implying that vision was better at a certain time point in life). Otherwise the term reduced visual acuity should be used (or a subclass of that).
?source_value: Loss of visual acuity (implying that vision was better at a certain timepoint in life). Otherwise the term reduced visual acuity should be used (or a subclass of that)
?translation: Perte d'acuité visuelle (impliquant que la vision était meilleure à un certain moment de la vie). Dans le cas contraire, il convient d'utiliser le terme \acuité visuelle réduite\" (ou une sous-classe de ce terme)."@fr

?value: Facial contour, as viewed from the front, triangular in shape, with breadth at the temples and tapering to a narrow chin.
?source_value: Facial contour, as viewed from the front, triangular in shape, with breadth at the temples and tapering to a narrow chin
?translation: Contour du visage, vu de face, de forme triangulaire, large au niveau des tempes et s'effilant vers un menton étroit.@fr

?value: An abnormality of the appearance of the face caused by constant contraction of the lips leading to a puckered or pursed appearance.
?source_value: An abnormality of the appearance of the face caused by constant contraction of the lips leading to a puckered or pursed appearance
?translation: Une anomalie de l'apparence du visage causée par la contraction constante des lèvres, qui donne une apparence plissée ou pincée.@fr

?value: Pterygium colli is a congenital skin fold that runs along the sides of the neck down to the shoulders. It involves an ectopic fibrotic facial band superficial to the trapezius muscle. Excess hair-bearing skin is also present and extends down the cervical region well beyond the normal hairline.
?source_value: Pterygium colli is a congenital skin fold that runs along the sides of the neck down to the shoulders. It involves an ectopic fibrotic facial band superficial to the trapezius muscle. Excess hair-bearing skin is also present and extends down the cervical region well beyond the normal hairline
?translation: Le pterygium colli est un pli cutané congénital qui s'étend sur les côtés du cou jusqu'aux épaules. Il s'agit d'une bande faciale fibrotique ectopique superficielle au muscle trapèze. Un excès de peau portant les cheveux est également présent et s'étend dans la région cervicale bien au-delà de la ligne normale des cheveux.@fr

?value: Any deviation from the normal motor coordination of the eyes that allows for bilateral fixation on a single object.
?source_value: Any deviation from the normal motor coordination of the eyes that allows for bilateral fixation on a single object
?translation: Tout écart par rapport à la coordination motrice normale des yeux qui permet la fixation bilatérale d'un seul objet.@fr

?value: Underdevelopment of the malar prominence of the jugal bone (zygomatic bone in mammals), appreciated in profile, frontal view, and/or by palpation.
?source_value: Underdevelopment of the malar prominence of the jugal bone (zygomatic bone in mammals), appreciated in profile, frontal view, and/or by palpation
?translation: Sous-développement de la proéminence malaire de l'os jugal (os zygomatique chez les mammifères), apprécié de profil, de face et/ou à la palpation.@fr

?value: Underdevelopment of part or all of the male external reproductive organs (which include the penis, the scrotum and the urethra).
?source_value: Underdevelopment of part or all of the male external reproductive organs (which include the penis, the scrotum and the urethra)
?translation: Sous-développement d'une partie ou de tous les organes reproducteurs externes masculins (ce qui inclut le pénis, le scrotum et l'urètre)@fr

?value: Distance between the hairline (trichion) and the glabella (the most prominent point on the frontal bone above the root of the nose), in the midline, more than two SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between the hairline and the glabella.
?source_value: Distance between the hairline (trichion) and the glabella (the most prominent point on the frontal bone above the root of the nose), in the midline, more than two SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between the hairline and the glabella
?translation: Distance entre la ligne des cheveux (trichion) et la glabelle (le point le plus proéminent de l'os frontal au-dessus de la racine du nez), sur la ligne médiane, inférieure de plus de deux écarts-types à la moyenne. Alternativement, une distance apparemment réduite entre la ligne des cheveux et la glabelle.@fr

?value: Ears that are low-set and posteriorly rotated.
?source_value: Ears that are low-set (HP:0000369) and posteriorly rotated (HP:0000358)
?translation: Oreilles implantées bas (HP:0000369) et tournées vers l'arrière (HP:0000358).@fr

?value: An abnormality in voluntary or involuntary eye movements or their control.
?source_value: An abnormality in voluntary or involuntary eye movements or their control
?translation: une anomalie des mouvements oculaires volontaires ou involontaires.@fr

?value: A rudimentary tag of skin often containing ear tissue including a core of cartilage and located just anterior to the auricle (outer part of the ear).
?source_value: A rudimentary tag of skin often containing ear tissue including a core of cartilage and located just anterior to the auricle (outer part of the ear)
?translation: Étiquette rudimentaire de peau contenant souvent du tissu auriculaire, y compris un noyau de cartilage, et située juste en avant du pavillon de l'oreille (partie externe de l'oreille).@fr

?value: A progressive form of sensorineural hearing impairment.
?source_value: A progressive form of sensorineural hearing impairment
?translation: Une forme progressive de déficience auditive neurosensorielle@fr

?value: Presence of cysts at the corticomedullary junction of the kidney in combination with tubulointerstitial fibrosis.
?source_value: Presence of cysts at the corticomedullary junction of the kidney in combination with tubulointerstitial fibrosis
?translation: Présence de kystes à la jonction corticomédullaire du rein, en association avec une fibrose tubulo-interstitielle@fr

?value: The presence of a triangular form of the mouth.
?source_value: The presence of a triangular form of the mouth
?translation: La présence d'une forme triangulaire de la bouche@fr

?value: Increased susceptibility to otitis media, as manifested by recurrent episodes of otitis media.
?source_value: Increased susceptibility to otitis media, as manifested by recurrent episodes of otitis media
?translation: Une susceptibilité accrue à l'otite moyenne, se manifestant par des épisodes récurrents d'otite moyenne.@fr

?value: The presence of a bifid uterus.
?source_value: The presence of a bifid uterus

?value: Initial bilateral ptosis followed by limitation of eye movements in all directions and slowing of saccades.
?source_value: Initial bilateral ptosis followed by limitation of eye movements in all directions and slowing of saccades
?translation: Ptosis initial bilatéral suivi d'une limitation des mouvements oculaires dans toutes les directions et d'un ralentissement des saccades.@fr

?value: A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on one of the autosomes (i.e., the human chromosomes 1-22) in which a trait manifests in heterozygotes. In the context of medical genetics, an autosomal dominant disorder is caused when a single copy of the mutant allele is present. Males and females are affected equally, and can both transmit the disorder with a risk of 50% for each child of inheriting the mutant allele.
?source_value: A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on one of the autosomes (i.e., the human chromosomes 1-22) in which a trait manifests in heterozygotes. In the context of medical genetics, an autosomal dominant disorder is caused when a single copy of the mutant allele is present. Males and females are affected equally, and can both transmit the disorder with a risk of 50% for each child of inheriting the mutant allele
?translation: Un mode de transmission qui concerne les caractères associés à un gène porté par un autosome (c.-à-d., les chromosomes 1 à 22 chez l'être humain), et où le caractère se manifeste chez les porteurs hétérozygotes. Dans le cadre de la génétique médicale, une maladie autosomique dominante survient lorsqu’une seule copie de l’allèle muté est présente. Les hommes et les femmes sont touchés de la même manière, et peuvent tous deux transmettre la maladie avec un risque de 50 % que chaque enfant hérite de l’allèle muté@fr

?value: Reduced superior to inferior length of the nasal septum.
?source_value: Reduced superior to inferior length of the nasal septum
?translation: Réduction de la longueur supérieure/inférieure de la cloison nasale.@fr

?value: Penile length more than 2 SD above the mean for age.
?source_value: Penile length more than 2 SD above the mean for age
?translation: Longueur du pénis supérieure à 2 DS par rapport à l'âge@fr

?value: Chronic otitis media refers to fluid, swelling, or infection of the middle ear that does not heal and may cause permanent damage to the ear.
?source_value: Chronic otitis media refers to fluid, swelling, or infection of the middle ear that does not heal and may cause permanent damage to the ear
?translation: L'otite moyenne chronique désigne un liquide, un gonflement ou une infection de l'oreille moyenne qui ne guérit pas et peut causer des dommages permanents à l'oreille.@fr

?value: An abnormality of facial morphology characterized by a small mouth opening and constant contraction of the lips as if the patient were whistling.
?source_value: An abnormality of facial morphology characterized by a small mouth opening and constant contraction of the lips as if the patient were whistling
?translation: Une anomalie de la morphologie faciale caractérisée par une petite ouverture de la bouche et une contraction constante des lèvres comme si le patient sifflait.@fr

?value: Posterior displacement of the tongue into the pharynx, i.e., a tongue that is mislocalised posteriorly.
?source_value: Posterior displacement of the tongue into the pharynx, i.e., a tongue that is mislocalised posteriorly
?translation: Déplacement postérieur de la langue dans le pharynx, c'est-à-dire une langue mal localisée à l'arrière de la gorge@fr

?value: A type of abnormal location of the ears in which the position of the ears is characterized by posterior rotation (the superior part of the ears is rotated towards the back of the head, and the inferior part of the ears towards the front).
?source_value: A type of abnormal location of the ears in which the position of the ears is characterized by posterior rotation (the superior part of the ears is rotated towards the back of the head, and the inferior part of the ears towards the front)
?translation: Un type de localisation anormale des oreilles dans lequel la position des oreilles est caractérisée par une rotation postérieure (la partie supérieure des oreilles est tournée vers l'arrière de la tête, et la partie inférieure des oreilles vers l'avant).@fr

?value: Interpupillary distance less than 2 SD below the mean (alternatively, the appearance of an decreased interpupillary distance or closely spaced eyes).
?source_value: Interpupillary distance less than 2 SD below the mean (alternatively, the appearance of an decreased interpupillary distance or closely spaced eyes)
?translation: Une distance interpupillaire inférieure à 2 DS par rapport à la moyenne (ou l'apparition d'une distance interpupillaire réduite ou d'yeux très rapprochés)@fr

?value: An abnormality of the nasal tip.
?source_value: An abnormality of the nasal tip

?translation: Une forme d'hypoplasie développementale de la mandibule dans laquelle la mandibule est mal localisée postérieurement.@fr

?value: Paralysis of the external ocular muscles.
?source_value: Paralysis of the external ocular muscles

?value: Infants normally have two fontanels at birth, the diamond-shaped anterior fontanelle at the junction of the coronal and sagittal sutures, and the posterior fontanelle at the intersection of the occipital and parietal bones. The posterior fontanelle usually closes by the 8th week of life, and the anterior fontanel closes by the 18th month of life on average. This term applies if there is delay of closure of the fontanelles beyond the normal age.
?source_value: Infants normally have two fontanels at birth, the diamond-shaped anterior fontanelle at the junction of the coronal and sagittal sutures, and the posterior fontanelle at the intersection of the occipital and parietal bones. The posterior fontanelle usually closes by the 8th week of life, and the anterior fontanel closes by the 18th month of life on average. This term applies if there is delay of closure of the fontanelles beyond the normal age
?translation: Les nourrissons ont normalement deux fontanelles à la naissance, la fontanelle antérieure en forme de losange à la jonction des sutures coronale et sagittale, et la fontanelle postérieure à l'intersection des os occipital et pariétal. La fontanelle postérieure se ferme généralement vers la 8e semaine de vie, et la fontanelle antérieure se ferme vers le 18e mois de vie en moyenne. Ce terme s'applique en cas de retard de la fermeture des fontanelles au-delà de l'âge normal.@fr

?value: Midline indentation or cleft of the scrotum.
?source_value: Midline indentation or cleft of the scrotum
?translation: Indentation de la ligne médiane ou fente du scrotum@fr

?value: Distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border.
?source_value: Distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border
?translation: Distance entre la base nasale et le bord vermillon de la ligne médiane de la lèvre supérieure inférieure de plus de 2 ET à la moyenne. Ou encore, une distance apparemment réduite entre la base du nez et le bord vermillon de la ligne médiane de la lèvre supérieure.@fr

?value: Diffusely large eye (with megalocornea) associated with glaucoma.
?source_value: Diffusely large eye (with megalocornea) associated with glaucoma
?translation: Œil de grande taille diffuse (avec mégalocornée) associé à un glaucome@fr

?value: An abnormal difference between the left and right sides of the face.
?source_value: An abnormal difference between the left and right sides of the face
?translation: Une différence anormale entre les côtés gauche et droit du visage.@fr

?value: Anterior and inferior folding of the upper portion of the ear that obliterates triangular fossa and scapha.
?source_value: Anterior and inferior folding of the upper portion of the ear that obliterates triangular fossa and scapha
?translation: Pliage antérieur et inférieur de la partie supérieure de l'oreille qui oblitère la fosse triangulaire et le scapha.@fr

?value: An endocrine tumor of the pancreas that secretes excessive amounts of glucagon.
?source_value: An endocrine tumor of the pancreas that secretes excessive amounts of glucagon
?translation: Une tumeur endocrine du pancréas qui sécrète des quantités excessives de glucagon@fr

?value: Hypogonadotropic hypogonadism is characterized by reduced function of the gonads (testes in males or ovaries in females) and results from the absence of the gonadal stimulating pituitary hormones: follicle stimulating hormone (FSH) and luteinizing hormone (LH).
?source_value: Hypogonadotropic hypogonadism is characterized by reduced function of the gonads (testes in males or ovaries in females) and results from the absence of the gonadal stimulating pituitary hormones: follicle stimulating hormone (FSH) and luteinizing hormone (LH)
?translation: L'hypogonadisme hypogonadotrope est caractérisé par une fonction réduite des gonades (testicules chez l'homme, ovaires chez la femme) et résultant de la diminution des hormones gonadotrophiques : hormones folliculo-stimulante (FSH) et lutéinisante (LH)@fr

?value: Hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, occurring in the face.
?source_value: Hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, occurring in the face
?translation: Hémangiome, une tumeur bénigne des cellules endothéliales vasculaires, survenant au niveau du visage.@fr

?value: High urine phosphate in the presence of hypophosphatemia.
?source_value: High urine phosphate in the presence of hypophosphatemia
?translation: Phosphates urinaires élevés en présence d'une hypophosphatémie.@fr

?value: An abnormality of the anterior fontanelle, i.e., the cranial fontanelle that is located at the intersection of the coronal and sagittal sutures.
?source_value: An abnormality of the anterior fontanelle, i.e., the cranial fontanelle that is located at the intersection of the coronal and sagittal sutures
?translation: Une anomalie de la fontanelle antérieure, c'est-à-dire la fontanelle qui se trouve à l'intersection des sutures coronale et sagittale.@fr

?value: Interalar distance more than 2 SD below the mean for age, or alternatively, an apparently decreased width of the nasal base and alae.
?source_value: Interalar distance more than 2 SD below the mean for age, or alternatively, an apparently decreased width of the nasal base and alae
?translation: Distance interalaire inférieure de plus de 2 DS à la moyenne pour l'âge, ou alternativement, une largeur apparemment réduite de la base nasale et des alae.@fr

?value: Height of the palate more than 2 SD above the mean (objective) or palatal height at the level of the first permanent molar more than twice the height of the teeth (subjective).
?source_value: Height of the palate more than 2 SD above the mean (objective) or palatal height at the level of the first permanent molar more than twice the height of the teeth (subjective)
?translation: Hauteur du palais supérieure à 2 DS au-dessus de la moyenne (objectif) ou hauteur palatine au niveau de la première molaire permanente supérieure à deux fois la hauteur des dents (subjectif).@fr

?value: Atrophy of the choroid and retinal layers of the fundus.
?source_value: Atrophy of the choroid and retinal layers of the fundus
?translation: Atrophie de la choroïde et des couches rétiniennes du fond de l'œil@fr

?value: An anomaly in the placement or shape of the hairline (trichion) on the forehead, that is, the border between skin on the forehead that has head hair and that does not.
?source_value: An anomaly in the placement or shape of the hairline (trichion) on the forehead, that is, the border between skin on the forehead that has head hair and that does not
?translation: Anomalie de l'emplacement ou de la forme de la ligne d'implantation des cheveux (trichion) sur le front, c'est-à-dire la limite entre la peau du front qui a des cheveux et celle qui n'en a pas.@fr

?value: Width of the forehead or distance between the frontotemporales is more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or apparently increased distance between the two sides of the forehead.
?source_value: Width of the forehead or distance between the frontotemporales is more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or apparently increased distance between the two sides of the forehead
?translation: Largeur du front ou distance entre les frontotemporaux supérieure à deux écarts-types au-dessus de la moyenne (objective) ; ou distance apparemment accrue entre les deux côtés du front.@fr

?value: An abnormality of refraction characterized by the ability to see objects nearby clearly, while objects in the distance appear blurry.
?source_value: An abnormality of refraction characterized by the ability to see objects nearby clearly, while objects in the distance appear blurry
?translation: Anomalie de la réfraction caractérisée par la capacité à voir clairement les objets proches, alors que les objets éloignés apparaissent flous.@fr

?value: An abnormality of the sensory perception of sound.
?source_value: An abnormality of the sensory perception of sound
?translation: Une anomalie de la perception sensorielle du son@fr

?value: High urine potassium in the presence of hypokalemia.
?source_value: High urine potassium in the presence of hypokalemia
?translation: Potassium urinaire élevé en présence d'hypokalémie@fr

?value: Paralysis of one or more extraocular muscles that are responsible for eye movements.
?source_value: Paralysis of one or more extraocular muscles that are responsible for eye movements
?translation: Paralysie d'un ou de plusieurs muscles extraoculaires responsables des mouvements oculaires.@fr

?value: Facial myokymia is a fine fibrillary activity of one or more muscles innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve).
?source_value: Facial myokymia is a fine fibrillary activity of one or more muscles innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve)
?translation: La myokymie faciale est une activité fibrillaire fine d'un ou plusieurs muscles innervés par le nerf facial (le septième nerf crânien).@fr

?value: Glaucoma refers loss of retinal ganglion cells in a characteristic pattern of optic neuropathy usually associated with increased intraocular pressure.
?source_value: Glaucoma refers loss of retinal ganglion cells in a characteristic pattern of optic neuropathy usually associated with increased intraocular pressure
?translation: Le glaucome entraine une perte de cellules ganglionnaires de la rétine caractéristique d'une neuropathie optique généralement associée à une augmentation de la pression intraoculaire.@fr

?value: Abnormality of the adrenal glands, i.e., of the endocrine glands located at the top of the kindneys.
?source_value: Abnormality of the adrenal glands, i.e., of the endocrine glands located at the top of the kindneys
?translation: Anomalie des glandes surrénales, c'est-à-dire des glandes endocrines situées au dessus des reins@fr

?value: A facial appearance characterized by a permanently or nearly permanently opened mouth.
?source_value: A facial appearance characterized by a permanently or nearly permanently opened mouth
?translation: Aspect du visage caractérisé par une ouverture permanente ou quasi permanente de la bouche.@fr

?value: Accumulation of clear fluid in the between the layers of membrane (tunica vaginalis) surrounding the testis.
?source_value: Accumulation of clear fluid in the between the layers of membrane (tunica vaginalis) surrounding the testis
?translation: Épanchement de liquide dans la membrane séreuse (tunique vaginale) qui enveloppe les testicules@fr

?value: An abnormal bluish coloration of the sclera.
?source_value: An abnormal bluish coloration of the sclera
?translation: Coloration bleutée anormale de la sclérotique@fr

?value: Any abnormality of the palate, i.e., of roof of the mouth.
?source_value: Any abnormality of the palate, i.e., of roof of the mouth
?translation: Toute anomalie du palais, c'est-à-dire du toit de la bouche.@fr

?value: Nasal ridge curving anteriorly to an imaginary line that connects the nasal root and tip. The nose appears often also prominent, and the columella low.
?source_value: Nasal ridge curving anteriorly to an imaginary line that connects the nasal root and tip. The nose appears often also prominent, and the columella low
?translation: Crête nasale s'incurvant vers l'avant jusqu'à une ligne imaginaire qui relie la racine et la pointe nasale. Le nez apparaît souvent aussi proéminent, et la columelle basse@fr

?value: An area of depressed vision located at the point of fixation and that interferes with central vision.
?source_value: An area of depressed vision located at the point of fixation and that interferes with central vision
?translation: Une zone de dépression visuelle située au point de fixation et qui interfère avec la vision centrale.@fr

?value: Absence of fleshy non-cartilaginous tissue inferior to the tragus and incisura.
?source_value: Absence of fleshy non-cartilaginous tissue inferior to the tragus and incisura
?translation: Absence de tissu charnu non cartilagineux à l'arrière du tragus et de l'incisif.@fr

?value: The presence of a gonadoblastoma of the testis.
?source_value: The presence of a gonadoblastoma of the testis
?translation: Présence d'un gonadoblastome dans les testicules@fr

?value: An abnormality of the ovulation cycle.
?source_value: An abnormality of the ovulation cycle

?value: Nephrotic syndrome is a collection of findings resulting from glomerular dysfunction with an increase in glomerular capillary wall permeability associated with pronounced proteinuria. Nephrotic syndrome refers to the constellation of clinical findings that result from severe renal loss of protein, with Proteinuria and hypoalbuminemia, edema, and hyperlipidemia.
?source_value: Nephrotic syndrome is a collection of findings resulting from glomerular dysfunction with an increase in glomerular capillary wall permeability associated with pronounced proteinuria. Nephrotic syndrome refers to the constellation of clinical findings that result from severe renal loss of protein, with Proteinuria and hypoalbuminemia, edema, and hyperlipidemia
?translation: Le syndrome néphrotique est un ensemble d'observations résultant d'un dysfonctionnement glomérulaire avec une augmentation de la perméabilité de la paroi capillaire glomérulaire associée à une protéinurie prononcée. Le syndrome néphrotique désigne la constellation d'observations cliniques résultant d'une perte rénale grave de protéines, avec protéinurie et hypoalbuminémie, œdème et hyperlipidémie.@fr

?value: Any abnormality of the parotid glands, which are the salivary glands that are located in the subcutaneous tissues of the face overlying the mandibular ramus and anterior and inferior to the external ear.
?source_value: Any abnormality of the parotid glands, which are the salivary glands that are located in the subcutaneous tissues of the face overlying the mandibular ramus and anterior and inferior to the external ear
?translation: Toute anomalie des glandes parotides, qui sont des glandes salivaires situées dans les tissus sous-cutanés de la face, au-dessus de la branche mandibulaire et en avant et en dessous de l'oreille externe.@fr

?value: An anomaly of the midface, which is a region and not an anatomical term. It extends, superiorly, from the inferior orbital margin to, inferiorly, the level of nasal base. It is formed by the maxilla (upper jaw) and zygoma and cheeks and malar region. Traditionally, the nose and premaxilla are not included in the midface.
?source_value: An anomaly of the midface, which is a region and not an anatomical term. It extends, superiorly, from the inferior orbital margin to, inferiorly, the level of nasal base. It is formed by the maxilla (upper jaw) and zygoma and cheeks and malar region. Traditionally, the nose and premaxilla are not included in the midface
?translation: Une anomalie de la face moyenne, qui est une région et non un terme anatomique. Elle s'étend, en haut, du bord inférieur de l'orbite jusqu'au niveau de la base du nez, en bas. Elle est formée par le maxillaire (mâchoire supérieure) et le zygoma, ainsi que par les joues et la région malaire. Traditionnellement, le nez et le prémaxillaire ne sont pas inclus dans la face moyenne.@fr

?value: An eye that is protruding anterior to the plane of the face to a greater extent than is typical.
?source_value: An eye that is protruding anterior to the plane of the face to a greater extent than is typical
?translation: Un œil qui fait saillie vers l'avant par rapport au plan du visage dans une mesure plus importante que la norme.@fr

?value: A misalignment of the eyes so that the visual axes deviate from bifoveal fixation. The classification of strabismus may be based on a number of features including the relative position of the eyes, whether the deviation is latent or manifest, intermittent or constant, concomitant or otherwise and according to the age of onset and the relevance of any associated refractive error.
?source_value: A misalignment of the eyes so that the visual axes deviate from bifoveal fixation. The classification of strabismus may be based on a number of features including the relative position of the eyes, whether the deviation is latent or manifest, intermittent or constant, concomitant or otherwise and according to the age of onset and the relevance of any associated refractive error
?translation: Un défaut d'alignement des yeux tel que les axes visuels s'écartent de la fixation bifovéale. La classification du strabisme peut se fonder sur un certain nombre de caractéristiques, notamment la position relative des yeux, le caractère latent ou manifeste, intermittent ou constant, concomitant ou non, l'âge d'apparition et la pertinence de toute erreur de réfraction associée.@fr

?value: An abnormality of the uvea, the vascular layer of the eyeball.
?source_value: An abnormality of the uvea, the vascular layer of the eyeball
?translation: Une anomalie de l'uvée, la couche vasculaire du globe oculaire@fr

?value: The emission of semen and seminal fluid into the bladder instead of through the penis during orgasm.
?source_value: The emission of semen and seminal fluid into the bladder instead of through the penis during orgasm
?translation: Émission de sperme et de fluide séminal dans la vessie, plutôt qu'à travers le pénis, lors de l'orgasme@fr

?value: An anomaly of the pineal gland,a small endocrine gland in the brain that produces melatonin.
?source_value: An anomaly of the pineal gland,a small endocrine gland in the brain that produces melatonin
?translation: Une anomalie de la glande pinéale, la petite glande endocrine dans le cerveau qui produit la mélatonine@fr

?value: The presence of multiple cysts at the border between the renal cortex and medulla.
?source_value: The presence of multiple cysts at the border between the renal cortex and medulla
?translation: La présence de multiples kystes à la frontière entre le cortex rénal et la zone médullaire@fr

?value: An abnormal configuration of the lower lip such that it is turned outward i.e., everted, with the Inner aspect of the lower lip vermilion (normally opposing the teeth) being visible in a frontal view.
?source_value: An abnormal configuration of the lower lip such that it is turned outward i.e., everted, with the Inner aspect of the lower lip vermilion (normally opposing the teeth) being visible in a frontal view
?translation: Configuration anormale de la lèvre inférieure telle qu'elle est tournée vers l'extérieur, c'est-à-dire éversée, l'aspect interne du vermillon de la lèvre inférieure (normalement en regard des dents) étant visible en vue frontale.@fr

?value: Abnormality of the iris characterized by, typically bilateral, complete or partial iris hypoplasia. The phenotype ranges from mild defects of anterior iris stroma only to almost complete absence of the iris.
?source_value: Abnormality of the iris characterized by, typically bilateral, complete or partial iris hypoplasia. The phenotype ranges from mild defects of anterior iris stroma only to almost complete absence of the iris
?translation: Anomalie de l'iris caractérisée par une hypoplasie complète ou partielle de l'iris, généralement bilatérale. Le phénotype va de légères anomalies du stroma de l'iris antérieur à l'absence quasi-totale de l'iris.@fr

?value: Inclination of the anterior surface of the forehead from the vertical more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or apparently excessive posterior sloping of the forehead in a lateral view.
?source_value: Inclination of the anterior surface of the forehead from the vertical more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or apparently excessive posterior sloping of the forehead in a lateral view
?translation: Inclinaison de la surface antérieure du front par rapport à la verticale supérieure à deux écarts-types au-dessus de la moyenne (objectif) ; ou inclinaison postérieure apparemment excessive du front en vue latérale.@fr

?value: An abnormality of the fovea centralis, the central area of the macula that mediates central, high resolution vision and contains the largest concentration of cone cells in the retina.
?source_value: An abnormality of the fovea centralis, the central area of the macula that mediates central, high resolution vision and contains the largest concentration of cone cells in the retina
?translation: Une anomalie de la fovéa centrale, la zone centrale de la macula qui assure la médiation de la vision centrale à haute résolution et qui contient la plus grande concentration de cônes de la rétine.@fr

?value: An abnormality of the retina characterized by pigment deposition. It is typically associated with migration and proliferation of macrophages or retinal pigment epithelial cells into the retina; melanin from these cells causes the pigmentary changes. Pigmentary retinopathy is a common final pathway of many retinal conditions and is often associated with visual loss.
?source_value: An abnormality of the retina characterized by pigment deposition. It is typically associated with migration and proliferation of macrophages or retinal pigment epithelial cells into the retina; melanin from these cells causes the pigmentary changes. Pigmentary retinopathy is a common final pathway of many retinal conditions and is often associated with visual loss
?translation: Anomalie de la rétine caractérisée par un dépôt de pigments. Elle est généralement associée à la migration et à la prolifération de macrophages ou de cellules épithéliales du pigment rétinien dans la rétine ; la mélanine de ces cellules est à l'origine des changements pigmentaires. La rétinopathie pigmentaire est une voie finale commune à de nombreuses affections rétiniennes et est souvent associée à une perte de vision.@fr
